article.headline: Appalachian St. 65, Furman 60
article.story: GREENVILLE, S.C. -- Josh Hunter and Ryann Abraham scored 13 points each, leading four players in double figures for Appalachian State in a 65-60 win against Furman on Wednesday night. Isaac Butts added 12 and Eduardo Bermudez chipped in 10 for the Mountaineers (3-2, 1-0 Southern Conference), who notched a victory in the conference opener for both teams. Hunter grabbed 11 rebounds and Butts added 10. Abraham was 3-for-6 from behind the arc. Jordan Miller led the Paladins (1-5, 0-1) with a game-high 17 points. Alex Opacic added 14 and grabbed a team-high seven rebounds. The Mountaineers shot 42.6 percent from the field (23 of 54) in the game, and outrebounded the Paladins 37-30 en route to victory. Furman, which led 34-29 at halftime, shot 38.9 percent (21 of 54) in the loss.
